    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="136"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/487.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to France</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Acting Secretary for Foreign Affairs today confirmed protest of Japan and Russia
                    against Article 16. French Foreign Office preparing memorandum recommending
                    entire suppression of this article, because it relates only to future business,
                    does not affect present loan, and would virtually create a monopoly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bacon</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
